Interface ViewGroupMvpViewStateDelegateCallback<V extends MvpView,P extends MvpPresenter<V>,VS extends ViewState<V>>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    MvpDelegateCallback<V,P>, MvpViewStateDelegateCallback<V,P,VS>, ViewGroupDelegateCallback<V,P>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MvpViewStateFrameLayout, MvpViewStateLinearLayout, MvpViewStateRelativeLayout

    public interface ViewGroupMvpViewStateDelegateCallback<V extends MvpView,P extends MvpPresenter<V>,VS extends ViewState<V>>
extends MvpViewStateDelegateCallback<V,P,VS>, ViewGroupDelegateCallback<V,P>
    * An enhanced version of MvpDelegateCallback that adds ViewState support. This interface must be implemented by all (subclasses of) android.view.View like FrameLayout that want to support ViewState and mvp.
    Since:
    3.0
